<p>I am inserting an <strong>SWT</strong> <code>Control</code> inside each row of <code>Table</code> via a <code>TableEditor</code> and I am seeing that sometimes GUI adjustments on the child control happen with ~1 second of delay.</p>  <p>As an example, pick a <code>Button</code> (FATAL logs are <code>Table</code>'s events, ERROR logs are <code>Button</code>'s event):</p>  <p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/GHbb8.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/GHbb8.png" alt="enter image description here"></a></p>  <p>I can see that e.g. on table initialization, re-sorting, new-row, usually the list of events that are called on a table's row is:</p>  <pre class="lang-java prettyprint-override"><code>TableItem.IMECOMPOSITION TableItem.ERASEITEM TableItem.MEASUREITEM TableItem.PAINT (~1 looooong second passes) Button.PAINT </code></pre>  <p>This is in line with <a href="https://www.eclipse.org/articles/article.php?file=Article-CustomDrawingTableAndTreeItems/index.html" rel="nofollow">what I knew</a> (well, not the button thing), but I would like to understand:</p>  <ul> <li><em>why</em> is the event on the child-button delayed?</li> <li><em>how</em> to systematically synchronize the PAINTing of all children of an SWT control/table/tree/[...].</li> </ul>